metadata.name: Threads: An algorithm study #35
metadata.description:
This series of my algorithmic studies is an exploration of animation algorithms to create an abstract artwork using connected lines.
This artwork is created with only lines and shadows to create a sense of connected threads with a special algorithm. Multiple color palettes have been used. It takes a short time for animation to complete.

Made with p5js.

metadata.name: Confini #99
metadata.description:
This is my last fxhash piece for a while, so that I can focus on my personal life. I tried to make a piece that creates the appearance of shapes scratched into the canvas. There are three carefully selected color palettes. One of them is heavily inspired by "Self-Portrait with Bandaged Ear and Pipe", by Van Gogh. These are heavily contrasting colors that I tried to get to work in coherence. One of the color palettes exists out of flavorful colors and means to spark joy in the viewer (depending on the outcome). The final color palette is one that is meant to evoke nothing but calmness. The colors are meant to remind of nature and serenity. I hope you enjoy my work.

Made in p5.js

By twistie

metadata.name: Sketch F #532
metadata.description:
Sketch is an open-ended series. Works evolve as I code a generative project, sometimes drastically. Intermediate works usually don't see the light of day - they get archived and forgotten. This series is snapshots of different forms along the way - each standing alone, but also part of a larger meandering work flow. The word Sketch implies incompleteness. This project may end up being two works, or it could evolve for years. Part of the joy of generative art is never knowing what's around the corner. I have no set schedule. There may be multiple Sketches released a week, or it could be weeks or months between drops. I have no idea where Sketch is heading and there is no guarantee of cohesiveness from Sketch to Sketch. Color palettes and forms will change as new ideas are explored.

Sketch F(ree). A gift to all Sketch A-E collectors. The underlying grid structure from A-E remains, but more variation on size and distribution is added. Many more color palettes are introduced. Grid size, padding, and colors vary.

metadata.name: INTERFERENCES #3
metadata.description:
INTERFERENCES is an abstract representation of the incredible collaboration between artists, collectors and developers on fxhash.

Each edition is composed of a multitude of lines representing each individual on the platform. The color of each line defines the role of each individual in this universe. Through their interactions, and the interferences they produce, each line participates in the creation of a common work.

Happy birthday fxhash! And congratulations to all those who work for its success.

Primary sales are donated to the Processing Foundation

[TOUCHSCREEN]
* Double Tap to save the current image

[KEYBOARD]
* Press [S] to save the current image
* Press [1] to save a 1500x2000 pixels PNG
* Press [2] to save a 3000x4000 pixels PNG
* Press [3] to save a 6000x8000 pixels PNG
* Press [0] to save 3 individual SVG for each color set of lines + the background image PNG
* Press [9] to save a grouped SVG of all the lines + the background image PNG

Artist: Estienne
Nov. 2022
NFT License 2.0

Credits to Piter Pasma (@piterpasma) for the Reumann-Witkam line simplification algorithm used in this generator

metadata.name: Extrusion - v2 #101
metadata.description:
Dear collectors,
Extrusion was originally published as Project #14512 on June 9, 2022.
(https://www.fxhash.xyz/generative/14512)
Due to a technical issue, Project #14512 has been hidden from the site and is being replaced by this reissued version.

_______________________________

Extrusion is a work that brings the generation of particles that perform smooth sinusoidal movements according to the evolution of the animation frames. Each frame registers its position with a slight shading, and with continuous stacking we get the impression of depth that I like to call 'pseudo-3D'.
The perception of movement is something that I really enjoy watching and I hope it can have the same effect on collectors and enthusiasts of animated arts. Even so, for those who prefer static art, the work is finished after a frame count (which may vary depending on its hash) by adding a grain texture followed by a thin black beveled frame with white passe-partout for better highlighting. the post-animation result.

The palette sets were carefully chosen, totaling 19 palettes with 6 colors each, separated into themes of environment, mood, styles, materials and other elements. Of these seven are monochromatic sets with a small rarity of being obtained.

The shapes of the particles vary between 8 pointed stars (rare), circles and vertical or horizontal bars and their trail changes a lot according to the frame count and total number of objects in the scene. Sometimes they look like they are dancing while moving around creating pseudo-three-dimensional objects.

The screens can be obtained in three different aspect ratios: 1x1 (square, more common), and two wide options (16x9 landscape and 9x16 portrait, a little rarer).

As already said and I always say: carefully chosen palettes!

_______________________________
Variety of editions is guaranteed by several features:
* Black or white backgrounds (for better highlighting of particles);
* 19 color palettes with 6 colors each where the rarest is BW (<6%)
* 3 aspect ratios: 1x1 (50%), 9x16 (25%) and 16x9 (25%)
* Controlled variety of scale;
* Controlled variety of particle number;
* Animation time;
* Shape type: circles (60%), bars (30%) and stars (10%);
* Animation with coordinated movement (12%);
* Super rare inverted move (5%)

_______________________________
Interactive instructions:
* Press [I] to change the inverted mode, if you have it.

_______________________________
Saving your .png file:
* Press [S] to save your .png file in screen size;
* Press [0] to save your .png file in qHD resolution;
* Press [1] to save your .png file in FHD resolution;
* Press [2] to save your .png file in UHD (4K) resolution;
* Press [3] to save your .png file in FUHD (8K) resolution;
(for higher resolutions, please wait up for few seconds until complete render)


Made with p5.js
_______________________________
Creator: Kukuti
June 2022 -> Dec2022
License: NFT 2.0

metadata.name: BINARY WORDS #251
metadata.description:
I drew my first 8x8 pixel binary image on 11/08/2022 with 'iloveyou' encoded for my wife, it was our 10-year anniversary on this day.  After that made this generative stuff for fxhash's birthday bash.

#fxhashturnsone

Donations:
25% to ThreeJs team

The image contains a binary coded word or phrase with a length of 8 characters. The grays represents 0, the other colors represents 1. One row -> one character. Should be proceed decoding from left to right and from top to bottom.

An example: 'iloveyou'

01101001
01101100
01101111
01110110
01100101
01111001
01101111
01110101

The fxrandom selects a word and the program converts it to binary data. After that, the background (ground and sky) is randomly generated from color schemes. Then the binary gray colors are drawn. Also the color of light next to null colors is randomly generated from color schemes. Random affects also the animation.

The animation stops when you do these interactions below, then restarts after a few seconds of inactivity.

Press spacebar to change:

- frame view -> without frame
- without frame -> original 8x8px size
- original 8x8px size -> frame view

Press 's' to save an svg from current view.

Notes:
- Build with ReactJs and TweenJs
- Every upcoming day, half of the remaining pieces are burned.

Happy Birthday fxhash community!
I'm glad to be among you!

metadata.name: what's left of what's left #17
metadata.description:
"The images is not a closed field of knowledge; it is a whirling, centrifugal field. It is not a fiedl of knowledge like any other; it is a movement demanding all the anthropogical aspects of being and time" Didi-Huberman

Continuing in the experimentation of photography and generative art.

What's left of what's left ... Seeks to take the reflection beyond the simple superimposition of images, highlighting the "human" x "machine" interaction.

The areas of light, fog and shadows present us with image clippings in a large tangle of visual reflections.

The algorithm builds unique images from the combination of different layers, according to a bank of photographs extracted from my own collection. In total, there are six layers containing 10 photographs each, in addition to a base layer containing 20 photos of urban fragments.

In addition, the code implements, in a random and semi-autonomous way, some adaptations such as masking, colorization, rotation and blending modes for specific layers.

* Features
Place - Where have i been. 20 distinct urban fragments;
Mode - “Color” 80% or “B&W” 20%;
Zone - “Amazon” 25%; “Mist” and “Terracotta” 20%, “Old Sky” 15%; and “Ocher” and “Golden” 10%.
Invert - 2.5%

"In a sense of overlapping past/future, not as an idea of ​​current time, but as places of memory dispute. This "non-place", traversed by layers, is solidified in the images, almost like a truce from the endless war of this inconstancy.
there is no winner" Raffa Gomes

Generative Token by of Morbeck for fxhash

august 21, 2022
